The JMPD says a number of passengers have been left injured. JOHANNESBURG One person has been killed in a taxi crash in Midrand on the N1 South, before the Buccleuch interchange.The Johannesburg Metro Police Department (JMPD) says a number of passengers have been left injured.It s understood authorities found the minibus on its side. JMPD spokesperson Wayne Minnaar says traffic has been affected. One male passenger has died. There s still an obstruction and motorists are advised to look out for the accident scene. There are lane restrictions on the N1 South, so motorists must just be on the lookout.&quot;